<HEAD>LaserPhoto BK-4</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 36-year-old truck driver remained in
police custody today after seizing a baby girl at gunpoint for two
hours, authorities said.
   Local newspapers said Lamyong Ruangwong grabbed the 18-month-old
baby from its grandparents at a downtown Bangkok house on
Wednesday, then wandered through the streets brandishing a pistol
while he held the girl in one arm.
