<NOTE>Senate Panel Takes Up Bills to Arrange Referendum on Status</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A move that could lead to statehood for Puerto
Rico is picking up speed in Congress.
   A Senate committee on Thursday began considering legislation
that would allow Puerto Rican voters to choose independence,
statehood or more autonomy while remaining a U.S. commonwealth.
   ``The process we begin today is designed to give the people of
Puerto Rico realistic options from which they can choose and expect
that an option will be implemented,'' said Sen. Bennett Johnston,
D-La., chairman of the Committee on Energy and Natural Resources.
   The three major political parties on Puerto Rico had requested
the legislation.
