<HEAD>Four Die in Crash of Hospital Helicopter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RAPELJE, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A medical helicopter ferrying an injured
rancher to a hospital crashed, killing all four people aboard,
authorities said today.
   Wreckage of the helicopter from St. Vincent Hospital in Billings
was found by searchers about 5:15 a.m. less than a mile from the
ranch house where the aircraft had landed late Thursday, said
George Ames, a Sweet Grass County undersheriff.
   ``There was nothing left of it,'' Ames said.
   One of the victims was rancher Tommy Kalberg, believed to be in
his 50s, who had been injured in an accident involving a
three-wheeled recreational vehicle, Ames said.
   Also aboard were the pilot, a nurse and an emergency medical
technician, he said. Authorities did not immediately release their
names.
   People at the ranch told authorities that the weather was good
when the helicopter took off and that there did not appear to be
anything wrong with the aircraft, Ames said.
