<TEXT>
   A large chunk of concrete fell from the
underside of a major New York City expressway, killing a motorist
when it crashed into the roof of his car, police said today.
   A portion of the FDR Drive, an elevated roadway that winds along
the east edge of Manhattan, was closed after the 10-by-5-foot chunk
