<FIRST>r a PM-ExposedBoys     06-02 0317</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Exposed Boys,0325</SECOND>
<HEAD>Newspaper: School Official Suspended For Making Boys Expose Themselves</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An assistant principal has been
suspended for disciplining two sixth-grade boys by making them
expose themelves in the presence of a male teacher and two other
boys, a newspaper reported today.
   The two sixth-graders were being reprimanded for pulling at each
other's pants in a classroom in front of other youngsters, the New
Haven Register quoted sources as saying.
   Patricia Lyons, the assistant principal at Sheridan Middle
School, was not present when the youngsters exposed themselves in
her office as she had ordered, the newspaper said. She apparently
was trying to teach the boys a lesson.
   Lyons was suspended with pay May 26, a day after the incident,
pending a hearing scheduled for next week before Superintendent
John Dow Jr., according to Tom Ragozzino, president of the school
administrators' union.
   The union will fight the suspension, Ragozzino said.
   A person who answered the phone today at Lyons' home identified
herself as the assistant principal's daughter, but wouldn't give
her name. She said her mother did not know why she's been suspended
and that she would take the matter to court, if necessary. She said
her mother was out and took a message.
   According to the Register, the two youngsters who were
disciplined were sent to Lyons' office along with two other
youngsters who witnessed the pants-pulling incident in a classroom.
Lyons then called a male teacher into her office and left the room,
first telling the boys to expose themselves in the presence of the
others.
   The newspaper said it was unclear whether the others saw the
boys expose themselves.
   Parents of the youngsters protested to school officials.
   ``To tell students to perform an act that you are saying is
wrong doesn't make any sense,'' one parent told the newspaper.
``You don't help kids growing up with scare tactics.''
</TEXT>
