<HEAD>Two Gunmen Kill Union Leader</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen ambushed and killed a union
leader Friday while he was on his way to work, police said.
   Police identifed the victim as Jaime Figueroa, 36, vice
president of Ramitex Workers Union, which is affiliated with the
militant May First Movement. Figueroa died of a gunshot wound to
the face, said police officer Arnold Alabastro.
   Alabastro said Figueroa and his wife were waiting for a ride to
work near his home when one of two gunmen approached him from
behind and shot him at close range with a .45-caliber pistol.
   The gunman shot at the labor leader seven times, but Figueroa
was hit only once, Alabastro said. Figueroa's wife was not harmed.
The assailants fled in a commandeered pedicab.
   The motive for the killing was unknown, Alabastro said.
