<HEAD>Former Transport Minister Sentenced for Taking Bribes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The former transportation minister was
sentenced Friday to five years in prison for taking $870,000 in
bribes while in office, court officials said.
   Judge Hong suk-che at the Seoul District Criminal Court also
ruled that Cha Kyu-hun must give up the money he received in 1987.
Cha received the money in exchange for authorizing a local business
to build a golf course.
   The prosecution had demanded 10 years in prison and the
forfeiture of the money.
   Cha, 60, was arrested in December.
   Two other businessmen, who allegedly acted as intermediaries in
the bribery scandal, were given suspended sentences.
