<HEAD>Indonesian Illegal Immigrants Shaved Bald to Prevent Return</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Immigration officials are shaving
the heads of illegal immigrants from Indonesia before they are
deported so they can be identified if they return immediately, a
newspaper reported Friday.
   There are about 1 million illegal immigrants from Indonesia
working on plantations and construction sites in Malaysia,
according to the government. Immigration officials arrest and
deport many of the Indonesians, but many return within a few days.
   The New Straits Times daily on Friday quoted the Immigration
Department in Batu Pahat, about 120 miles south of Kuala Lumpur, as
saying officials have begun shaving deportees' heads.
   The first group, 30 men, was deported by boat from Batu Pahat on
Wednesday, the newspaper said.
