<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--MadMeterMaid     06-02 0200</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Mad Meter Maid,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>Meter Maid Accused of Threatening Motorist With Broken Bottle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A meter maid was charged with assault after
she allegedly armed herself with a broken bottle and threatened the
owner of an illegally parked truck, police said.
   Camille Barns, 21, started to write a ticket for a pickup parked
on the edge of the French Quarter on Thursday, but the owner sat on
the rear bumper so that she could not read the license plate, said
police spokesman John Bryson.
   Barns and the truck owner, Norman Percy, argued loudly as she
filled out the citation without the license number and put it on
the windshield, witnesses told police.
   Barns became enraged, broke a soft drink bottle and walked
toward Percy, saying she was going to cut him before she threw the
bottle into the back of the truck and fled with two other meter
readers in a city van, Bryson said.
   Police issued Barns a summons to appear in Municipal Court on
Monday to answer a charge of simple assault, Bryson said. Parking
officials were in a meeting and not available to comment on whether
Barns would be suspended, a spokeswoman said.
</TEXT>
