<HEAD>Mary Martin Cancels Musical Tour</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mary Martin, who became famous on Broadway in
``South Pacific'' and ``Peter Pan,'' has withdrawn from a tour of
the musical version of ``Our Town'' due to medical reasons,
according to a published report.
   The Daily News reported in its Friday editions that Martin, 76,
was to star in ``Grovers Corners'' when the tour was canceled after
she pulled out.
   Price Berkley, who publishes the Theatrical Index trade
newsletter, said the cancellation was a ``major disappointment
because she's one of the few who can still build a huge ticket
advance on her name alone.''
</TEXT>
