<FIRST>r f PM-TelexSpinoff     06-02 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Telex Spinoff,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Memorex Telex To Spin Off Telex Communications Unit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Telex Communications Inc. of Minneapolis has
been spun off to its managers and to shareholders of its parent
company, Memorex Telex NV of the Netherlands, it was announced.
   Terms of the deal for the communications equipment maker were
not immediately disclosed Tuesday. Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. was
the lead underwriter of the bond offering on behalf of the
management, according to Darrell Dyer, vice president and treasurer
of the company.
   Telex Communications has annual revenue of slightly more than
$100 million and more than 1,500 employees, with four factories in
Minnesota and one in Lincoln, Neb., the company said.
   Shareholders of Memorex Telex will receive cash and preferred
securities, some of which can be converted into common stock in
Telex Communications, the parent company said.
   The cash will be used to pay off bank debt and for working
capital, the Dutch company said.
</TEXT>
