<FIRST>r f BC-RetailSales-Table     06-02 0412</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Retail Sales-Table,0452</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Retail Sales, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the domestic sales reported Thursday by the nation's
largest general retailers for May and for their fiscal years to
date, as compared to 1988.
   Several top retailers do not report their sales monthly,
including: Federated Department Stores Inc. and Allied Stores
Corp., the Campeau Corp. units; R.H. Macy & Co.; and, Batus Inc.
Not all retailers have the same fiscal year.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>Sears, Roebuck and Co.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Four weeks ended May 27: $2.5 billion, up 5.3 percent from $2.38
billion.
   First 4 months: $10.12 billion, up 9.7 percent from $9.23
billion.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>K mart Corp.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Four weeks ended May 24: $2.19 billion, up 2.5 percent from
$2.14 billion.
   First 4 months: $8.26 billion, up 3.5 percent from $7.98 billion.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>Wal-Mart Stores Inc.</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Month of May: $2.03 billion, up 25 percent from $1.63 billion.
   First 4 months: $7.41 billion, up 25 percent from $5.91 billion.
</TEXT>
