<HEAD>London Shares Finish Slightly Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A late surge left share prices only slightly lower
Friday on the London Stock Exchange.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished with
a loss of 0.8 point, or 0.04 percent, at 2,103.4. The index had
been down as much as 22.9 points in early trading.
   Over the past two weeks, interest rates worries have led to a
decline in the index of 102.1 points, or 4.6 percent.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended the day 0.1 point lower
at 1,745.5. The Financial Times 500-share index fell 1.03 points to
close at 1,201.40.
   Volume rose to 635.9 million shares from 512.5 million shares on
Thursday.
   Fueling the afternoon rebound was news that U.S. employment grew
at a slower-than-expected pace in May. The data, interpreted as a
sign of a slowing economy, suggested the U.S. Federal Reserve may
have greater latitude to ease monetary policy.
</TEXT>
